README
====

An experimental Symfony 2.x Bundle for using Doctrine\ODM\MongoDB


INSTALL
====

  git clone git://github.com/poulikov/MongoDBBundle.git src/Bundle/MongoDBBundle

edit {application_name}/config/config.yml

  ..
  mongo.odm: ~

  OR

  mongo.odm:
    connection: 'mongodb://localhost:27017'
    params: { connected: true }
  

or for dev environment
# config_dev.yml
  mongo.odm:
    connection: 'mongodb://localhost:27017'
    params: { connected: true }
    prefix_db_name: dev_
  # all table names will be prefixed dev_

or for test environment
# config_test.yml
  mongo.odm:
    prefix_db_name: test_
or
  mongo.odm:
    suffix_db_name: _test

Thats it!
